The FA board said they noted Clarke’s concern. But rather than look fully into whether they had made the right decision, the FA are staying on the same course.

They claim that the hardcore loyal support who go to home and away games are not being disadvantaged and that filling Wembley is the over-riding priority.

England fans ambassador Kevin Miles said: ‘We have appealed in the right way through our council representative and it will be disappointing in the extreme if our complaints are effectively ignored. The FA have not heard the last about this.’

